Financial services group FirstRand reported results on Thursday for the year to end June 2018. Income from operations rose by 8% to R44.2 billion, headline earnings rose by 12% to R23.7 billion and the final dividend of R1.45 pushed up the total dividend for the year to R2.75 – an 8% increase. Alan Pullinger, CEO of FirstRand, joins Ryk van Niekerk on the Moneyweb@Midday show to unpack the group’s latest set of results and strategy going forward. <a href="https://iono.fm/e/600310">Content hosted by iono.fm</a>